article:
This is a 'list of Antarctic and subantarctic islands'.

* Antarctic islands are the islands around Antarctica situated south of the
  Antarctic Convergence, i.e., in the Antarctic region proper.
* Subantarctic islands are the islands around Antarctica situated north of and
  adjacent to the Antarctic Convergence.

According to the terms of the Antarctic Treaty, claims to sovereignty over lands
south of 60Â°S are not asserted. This includes some of the Antarctic islands and
none of the subantarctic ones.
